    <string name="info_bmr_calculator_title">BMR Calculator</string>
    <string name="all_about_bmr">BMR is a estimation about the amount of calories human uses during rest.
        This is called the resting metabolic rate. The Equation used here is the Revised Harris-Benedict Equation.
        This number usually represents 60-75% of total energy consumption. There is a Stress and Activity -factor that
        has been ignored in this version of the calculation. More on that on the link below.</string>
    <string name="link_bmr"><a href="https://globalrph.com/medcalcs/harris-benedict-equation-updated-basal-metabolic-rate/">BMR Link Here</a></string>
    <string name="info_met_calculator_title">MET Calculator</string>
    <string name="all_about_met">MET stands for Metabolic EquivalenT this calculator counts how many
        calories you use per minute based on your weight the activity you are doing.
        The number estimations for each activity can be found on the link below.
        The calculations are based on them.</string>
    <string name="met_reference">Reference: American College of Sports Medicine. The Compendium of Physical Activities.
        ACSM Resource Manual 5th Edition, 2006. </string>
    <string name="link_met"><a href="http://media.hypersites.com/clients/1235/filemanager/MHC/METs.pdf">MET Table Link Here</a></string>

